article.description: — Jordan King scored 24 points as Richmond beat Queens 90-61 on Saturday night.
article.headline: King scores 24, Richmond defeats Queens University 90-61
article.linkText: King scores 24, Richmond defeats Queens University 90-61
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- — Jordan King scored 24 points as Richmond beat Queens 90-61 on Saturday night. King was 10 of 19 shooting (3 for 8 from 3-point range) for the Spiders (4-2). Neal Quinn scored 21 points while going 10 of 13 from the field, and added five rebounds. Isaiah Bigelow shot 5 for 9, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 11 points, while adding nine rebounds. Deyton Albury led the way for the Royals (3-4) with 22 points, eight rebounds, four assists and two blocks. Queens also got 12 points from Chris Ashby. AJ McKee also had 10 points, eight rebounds and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
